    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Prices vary by tutor experience and qualifications. Newer tutors typically charge $15–$20 per 30-minute session, while highly experienced tutors with specialized credentials may charge $25 or more.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">You can also purchase "Verbling Credits" in packages. Buying more credits at once often gives you a small discount. However, unlike iTalki where you pay tutors directly, Verbling acts as an intermediary — this means you pay slightly more for the convenience and quality assurance.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Key Features</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Verbling Flex</strong> — Book instant lessons with available tutors, 24/7</li>
      <li><strong>Verbling Go</strong> — Join group classes with other learners (4–8 students per class)</li>
      <li><strong>Tutor profiles</strong> — View detailed bios, video introductions, reviews, and specializations</li>
      <li><strong>Curriculum matching</strong> — Tutors can follow structured curricula for business English, exam prep, or conversation</li>
      <li><strong>Built-in video</strong> — No need to install software; lessons happen directly in your browser</li>
      <li><strong>Mobile app</strong> — Practice on the go with iOS and Android apps</li>
      <li><strong>Community features</strong> — Practice with other learners through the Verbling community</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Pros</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Quality-vetted tutors</strong> — Verbling manually reviews and approves all tutors before they can teach on the platform</li>
      <li><strong>Verbling Flex convenience</strong> — Perfect for busy schedules; find a tutor available right now</li>
      <li><strong>Group classes available</strong> — More affordable option at $8–$15 per session</li>
      <li><strong>No software needed</strong> — Browser-based video means you can start learning in seconds</li>
      <li><strong>Strong tutor selection</strong> — Many tutors from native English-speaking countries with teaching certifications</li>
      <li><strong>Flexible lesson length</strong> — Choose 30, 45, or 60-minute sessions based on your needs</li>
      <li><strong>Good mobile experience</strong> — The app makes it easy to practice on your commute or lunch break</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Cons</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Higher prices than competitors</strong> — Verbling charges more than iTalki or Preply for similar sessions</li>
      <li><strong>Credit system confusion</strong> — Having to buy credits first adds an extra step compared to direct booking</li>
      <li><strong>Limited tutor pool</strong> — Fewer tutors on Verbling compared to larger marketplaces</li>
      <li><strong>No free community exchanges</strong> — Unlike italki, there is no free language exchange feature</li>
      <li><strong>Booking can be tricky</strong> — Popular tutors often have busy schedules and limited availability</li>
      <li><strong>Less transparency on tutor qualifications</strong> — Some tutors list extensive credentials while others have minimal information</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">How Verbling Compares to Competitors</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">When compared to <a href="/reviews/italki/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">iTalki</a>, Verbling is more expensive but offers stricter tutor quality controls. iTalki has a larger marketplace and cheaper options, but the quality varies more widely. Verbling's "Flex" feature, however, gives it an edge in convenience.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Compared to <a href="/reviews/preply/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Preply</a>, both platforms offer professional tutoring with vetted teachers. Preply's subscription model may be simpler for regular learners, while Verbling's credit system offers more flexibility for occasional users.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">For budget learners, <a href="/reviews/cambly/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Cambly</a> offers unlimited conversation practice for a flat monthly fee — but Cambly tutors are more casual. Verbling tutors are generally more professional and structured.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Verdict</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Verbling is a solid choice for learners who value quality over cost. The platform's vetting process means you're more likely to find a professional, experienced tutor. The Verbling Flex feature is genuinely useful — if you have unexpected free time, you can start learning English with a native speaker within minutes.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">However, Verbling is not the cheapest option. If budget is your main concern, you may find better value on <a href="/reviews/italki/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">iTalki</a> or <a href="/reviews/cambly/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Cambly</a>. But if you want professional instruction with the flexibility of instant lessons, Verbling delivers.</p>
    
